Concertgoers who wanted to get a free ticket to the event (unless they were willing to pay for a VIP ticket) had to complete a series of tasks, or “actions,” such as volunteering, emailing a world leader, making a phone call, or otherwise meaningfully raising awareness for the goal: ending poverty.
